Instruction: With Control Module 1 still disconnected from the rest of the chain, turn its switch ON and measure: (1) continuity between its two through‑path conductors (the pair that forms the series path from input to output); (2) continuity of its internal switch when ON (from input-side 12 V conductor to output-side 12 V conductor); and (3) whether its red indicator LED/resistor branch lights and shows correct voltage (~12 V across it) when you apply +12 V and 0 V from the PSU directly to its input pair. This will determine if Control Module 1’s internal series path or indicator circuitry is open or faulty.
