Instruction: Reconnect Control Module 1 correctly to the PSU. Leave Control Modules 2–8 and the Load module disconnected as a group. Then, starting from the output of Control Module 1, step-by-step connect and test each subsequent module in series: for each module n (2–8), temporarily connect its input pair only, turn its switch ON, and apply +12 V/0 V from the upstream module. Measure (a) whether 12 V appears at its output pair, and (b) whether its red indicator LED lights with about 12 V across the LED+resistor branch. Continue downstream until you reach a module whose output no longer shows 12 V or whose LED will not illuminate under correct input. This will localize which module first fails to pass power correctly.
